# Overview

The framework allows to run UI automated test cases on PFDA.
Description of the automated test cases (steps) are located here:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1hskd1tUgyA7e3LSlwvxvqTeLr4RJ7E3CnbAP-oaM88I/edit?usp=sharing


# Environment preparation

1. It is a Maven project.
Make sure Maven is installed on your machine.

2. Make sure Java (JRE and JDK) is installed on the machine where you are planning to
run the automated suites.
Works fine with "openjdk" ver. 1.8.*

3. Make sure Firefox is installed on the machine. Works fine with the version 58.0

4. Download the "geckodriver" file from here: "https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases"
Unpack the file to ".../precision-fda/test/functional/drivers" folder.

5. Edit the file "settings.conf" in the folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/"
if needed.

6. Edit the file "credentials.conf" in the folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/"
if needed.
The file is a container of test users data - credentials and user info.
Please pay attention: all passwords and URLs must be saved in environment variables.

For example for linux
the file is: /etc/environment
contains:
--------------------
PFDA_AT_USER_1_PASSWORD_LOC="some_password1"
PFDA_AT_USER_2_PASSWORD_LOC="some_password2"
PFDA_AT_USER_ADMIN_PASSWORD_LOC="some_password3"
PFDA_BASIC_AUTH_DNX_PASSWORD_LOC="some_password4"

PFDA_AT_USER_1_PASSWORD_DEV="some_password5"
PFDA_AT_USER_2_PASSWORD_DEV="some_password6"
PFDA_AT_USER_ADMIN_PASSWORD_DEV="some_password7"
PFDA_BASIC_AUTH_DNX_PASSWORD_DEV="some_password8"

PFDA_SERVER_URL_DEV="https://11.22.33.44"
PFDA_SERVER_URL_LOC="https://localhost:1234"

PFDA_PLATFORM_SERVER_URL_LOC="https://staging.dnanexus.com"
PFDA_PLATFORM_SERVER_URL_DEV="https://staging.dnanexus.com"
--------------------

The environment value is set as a parameter via test running from command line
(an example is below).
So if the environment parameter set as "loc" - the PFDA_START_URL_LOC will be used.


# Running

Using terminal: go to ".../precision-fda/test/functional/" folder.
Execute "mvn clean test -Dsuite=fullregression.xml -Dheadless=true -Denv=dev",

where:

"fullregression.xml" - the "suite" file, the file with description what exactly test
cases should be run and how they should be run.
The line "parallel="tests" thread-count="3"" means that the suite will be run in
parallel via 3 threads.

"Dheadless=true" means that the browser(s) will be run in the hidden mode (without GUI).
This parameter can be also defined in the file "settings.conf", but the value given by
command line has higher priority.

"Denv=dev" means that the "developer" environment should be used for testing (see section 6).
Possible values: "dev", "loc".

If the "env" parameter is not defined via command line - the default value will be used
("default_env" parameter in the "settings.conf" file).

If you would like to run some specific suite only (e.g. "Spaces" testing only) you have
to define appropriate test suite ("spaces.xml" for this example).
So the command will be like: "mvn clean test -Dsuite=spaces.xml -Dheadless=true -Denv=loc"


# Test reports

a. ".../precision-fda/test/functional/target/surefire-reports/html/index.html" - is an html
report of the last run.

b. The folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/target/debug-log/" contains full log files
and screenshots taken through testing.
